description:
&lt;p&gt;Bank Staff Nurse –Pre Operative Assessment &amp; Outpatients (RGN)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Join us on our bank as a Staff Nurse RGN in our Brentwood Hospital and play your part in building a healthier nation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nuffield HealthBrentwoodHospital has established itself as one of the leading providers of private healthcare, serving patients fromBrentwood, With excellent patient satisfaction rates, and a Good CQC rating we’re proud of our reputation for clinical excellence and outstanding care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our modern 42 bedded hospital, which was refurbished in 2017 specialises in fertility / assisted conception treatment, weight loss, cosmetic surgery and orthopaedics. However, we offer a wealth of exceptional clinical services for both private and NHS patients&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Role&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Whether you are currently in the NHS or a private setting, we’re sure you will find your career with us motivating and rewarding.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Like all of us at Nuffield Health, you do what you do because you care. Every one of our brilliant people is passionate about making a real difference. As a Staff Nurse you will;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Be part of a close-knit team headed by our matron. Working together and across departments when required&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- With our consultant-led service, you will be working directly with some of the best clinical talent around, gaining experience with new practices, equipment and facilities.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- You’ll interact with practitioners from other departments because you understand the importance of continuity in patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Person&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;To succeed as a BANK Staff Nurse in our Pre operative assessment &amp; Outpatientsyou will;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Have a registration with the appropriate governing body and have the qualifications and experience relevant to your registration, including NMC.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Have post-registration experience working on a Surgery warn and Outpatients&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Be an excellent communicator and team worker – plus be flexible and motivated.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Have the ability to fully understand each patient’s needs and provide individual attention.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Benefits&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Holiday in line with the Working Time Directive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Access to our Pension Scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Discounted gym membership at £15.00 a month that they need to set up directly with the club. Discount does not extend to partners and family members.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Location - Brentwood Essex&lt;br /&gt;Contract Type - BANK&lt;br /&gt;Salary - £16:00 per hour&lt;br /&gt;Closing date - 30th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
